The presidential candidate of KOWA Party, Sina Fagbenro-Byron, has vowed to set up an independent body of investigators with specific powers to reopen the alleged missing $16 billion meant for electricity projects during the government of a former President, Olusegun Obasanjo. Byron said the committee would also check all reports of corruption in the electricity sector to ensure effective prosecution. Decades of uncertainty on 40mw Dadin Kowa power NBET, firm sign power purchase pact on 40mw Dadin Kowa  plant Can Dadin Kowa 40mw deliver electricity soon?